{"key":"processedPost-10784500","value":{"id":10784500,"first":10782908,"last":10792084,"when":1249224630,"utime":"08/02/09 05:50 PM","content":"The fact is, you're casing a species that doesn't require a casing layer and benefits little from one, provided you maintain proper fruiting conditions.&nbsp; It's hard to give advice on something that isn't needed.<br /><br />The only way a casing helps with cubes is if you're failing to provide a humid environment, and are not misting enough or at the proper times.&nbsp; A casing layer can help in those cases, but with proper care, an uncased bulk substrate will perform as well as a cased one, and soaking/dunking has replaced the casing layer as a way to resupply moisture between flushes.<br />RR","title":"Re: putting on a casing layer","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}